name: PaymentCardReaderSession.Event
desc: Optional events you can observe during the card-reading process.

items.name: case cardDetected
items.desc: An event that indicates the reader detected the presence of a card.

items.name: case completed
items.desc: An event that indicates the reader completed the reading process.

items.name: case readCancelled
items.desc: An event that indicates the cancellation of the operation.

items.name: case readNotCompleted
items.desc: An event that indicates the read operation didnâ€™t finish.

items.name: case readyForTap
items.desc: An event that indicates the reader is ready for someone to move their card within range of the iPhone.

items.name: case removeCard
items.desc: An event that indicates the consumer can move the card away from the device.

items.name: case retry
items.desc: An event that indicates the UI triggered a retry.

items.name: static func == (PaymentCardReaderSession.Event, PaymentCardReaderSession.Event) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are equal.
